Subject: Force the default make goal to the PGXS build

The first target in the upstream Makefile is `dist`, which makes plain
`make` produce a source archive instead of compiling the extension. Debian
builds expect `make` to build the extension, so set the default goal to `all`.

--- a/Makefile
+++ b/Makefile
@@ -1,3 +1,5 @@
+.DEFAULT_GOAL := all
+
 MODULE_big = pg_regresql
 OBJS = pg_regresql.o
 EXTENSION = pg_regresql
